<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 19.</seg></opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">The Duke of Newcastle</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Lieutenant Governor
                                Gordon</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Downing Street,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 17, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> With reference to your despatch of the
                                18th of January last, I have the honor to acquaint you that her
                                Majesty’s government consider that you exercised a wise discretion
                                in allowing the accused persons in the case of the steamer
                                Chesapeake copies of the requisition and warrant to which you
                                refer.</p>
                            <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>NEWCASTLE.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>